Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urhionsligo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 513<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/02 11:35:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: More Wizard improvements and still nada for Mages! errrr</span><hr size=1> It only makes sense that wizards are upgraded first, Wezloc.  They are the caster's warriors.  All int casters will be based in relation to them.  The fact that wizards are getting extreme upgrades is indicative that we will be graced with the same in time to come. <p><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg" align="center"><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710">My Character Profile</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/02 11:38:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: More Wizard improvements and still nada for Mages! errrr</span><hr size=1> Wezloc, I'll admit that I don't know jack about the high-end game except what I read from you guys here, and it is therefore biased knowledge, but from what I've seen, Wizards need upgrades too, perhaps at lower levels more than at uppers.  But that doesn't mean they don't need some help.  This just helps them some more.<br>
<br>
If anything, perhaps being even further behind is a good thing in some ways.  Think if mages were upgraded first, then wizards, druids (whoever) would probably whine that mages are too powerful now (like they'd ever make us that way, but i'm just saying!), so nerf them!  Then we'd get nerfed AGAIN, and THEN improvements to other classes would come, and we wouldn't be as far ahead as if we got improved later, since then they would see something to &quot;catch up&quot; to.  Basically, if you are improved last, you have the greatest chance of being balanced against what has already been done, rather than being balanced against the &quot;old&quot; standard (which we aren't balanced against now anyways).<br>
<br>
So it might be a mixed blessing.  Maybe wishful thinking.  I certainly hope I'm not nuts about this (though that's possible too.)<br>
<br>
